page_title: Why doesn’t VOY mention prescription medications by name? – Voy
question: Why doesn't VOY mention prescription medications by name?
answer: At Voy, we're committed to providing you with the most appropriate and effective treatment for your weight loss journey. We don't mention specific prescription medications upfront because choosing the right treatment should always be made with your clinician once they know more about your circumstances. Advertising restrictions in the UK prevent us from presenting all of our treatment options until you've had a clinical consultation, ensuring you receive personalized advice based on your individual health profile.

page_title: Information about Wegovy – Voy
question: What is Wegovy?
answer: Wegovy contains a hormone called GLP-1 that occurs naturally in the gut. Its purpose is to regulate appetite and provide a feeling of fullness for an extended period, helping to reduce cravings and keep you satisfied after meals. By targeting the receptors responsible for appetite in the brain, this medication helps to lower the body's natural ‘set point’, which is the weight it strives to maintain. Since Wegovy reduces your appetite, it gives you the opportunity to make healthier choices and reduce your calorie intake to optimise your weight loss.

page_title: Information about Wegovy – Voy
question: How does Wegovy work?
answer: Wegovy works by reducing appetite, reducing cravings, and lowering your body's set point. This helps you to feel less hungry, make healthier choices, and lose more weight before reaching a plateau.

page_title: Information about Wegovy – Voy
question: How to take Wegovy?
answer: You need to inject Wegovy once a week (on the same day each week), under the skin. It should be injected in the abdomen (keep 5cm away from your belly button), upper legs or upper arms. We advise you to mix up your injection sites each week to minimise discomfort.

page_title: Information about Wegovy – Voy
question: How to store Wegovy?
answer: You can keep the pen for 6 weeks when stored at a temperature below 30°C or in a refrigerator (2°C to 8°C). Do not freeze your medication and keep it away from the freezer compartment. When not using the pen, keep the pen cap on to protect it from light. Start using your treatment within 7 days of receiving it and finish within 6 weeks from the date on the Voy pharmacy label. Dispose of used needles and finished pens in the provided sharps bin and do not dispose of via wastewater or household waste.

page_title: What is the treatment titration pathway? – Voy
question: How do I change my dose?
answer: You can adjust your dosage directly from your account. Based on your current dose, you'll have the option to increase, maintain, or lower the strength. If you still need help, please speak to our Customer Support Team either via livechat from your account, or by emailing help@joinvoy.com and our team will be there to support you. So that we can update your plan before your next order, please let us know at least 3 days before your next order if you'd like to make any changes. You can check your next order date and current strength in your account under Manage Plans and Orders. We're working hard to give you more flexibility and autonomy in your treatment plan, if you have any feedback or suggestions, we'd love to hear them, just speak to our team.

page_title: Information about Mounjaro – Voy
question: What is Mounjaro?
answer: Mounjaro is a new medication that activates the receptors of two hormones found in the digestive tract known as GLP-1 and GIP which increase after we eat. They combine to provide a feeling of fullness for an extended period. By also targeting receptors in the brain it helps to lower the ‘set point’ which is the weight it ordinarily strives to maintain. Mounjaro gives you the opportunity and makes it easier to opt for healthier choices to reduce your calorie intake to optimise your weight loss.

page_title: Information about Mounjaro – Voy
question: How does Mounjaro work?
answer: Mounjaro reduces appetite, reduces cravings, and reduces the set point, allowing for more weight loss before reaching a plateau.

page_title: Information about Mounjaro – Voy
question: Why is there excess liquid after my fourth dose?
answer: Every Mounjaro Kwikpen comes with four doses of medication and enough liquid to prime your pen before every dose. This means that you will see an excess of liquid in your pen after you’ve taken your four doses. This is to be expected and should not be something to worry about. Please do not attempt to take more than 4 doses of your medication, attempting to use your pen more than four times will lock your pen and you’ll no longer be able to access the liquid.

page_title: Information about Mounjaro – Voy
question: Where can I find the expiry date for my Mounjaro pen?
answer: You can find the expiry date of your medication on the side of your medication box. This will be shown as ‘EXP: DATE’. The expiry date refers to the end of the month that is noted.

page_title: Information about Mounjaro – Voy
question: How do I take Mounjaro?
answer: Mounjaro is injected once a week (on the same day each week), under the skin, in the subcutaneous fat. It should be injected in the abdomen, thigh or upper arm (it’s advisable to rotate to a slightly different part of your body each time you inject, this minimises potential discomfort/irritation). Please note that the medication is contained within the clear chamber in the pen, not the individual needles – these are used to deliver each dose.

page_title: Information about Mounjaro – Voy
question: How to store your Mounjaro?
answer: You should store Mounjaro in the refrigerator between 2°C to 8°C (36°F to 46°F). If needed, each pen can be stored at room temperature up to 30°C ( 86°F) for up to 30 days. Once you've started the pen, it must be used within 30 days of the first dose. These instructions are supplementary to the information provided in the patient information leaflet in your medication box provided with each order.

page_title: General Guidance for Missing Doses – Voy
question: What should I do if I missed 1 dose of my treatment?
answer: You can take it as soon as you remember and continue your injections on this day moving forward. Alternatively, you can wait until your next scheduled dose and administer it then.

page_title: General Guidance for Missing Doses – Voy
question: What should I do if I missed more than 2 doses of my treatment?
answer: Please contact our clinical team, as a dose adjustment to a lower strength may be needed to ensure your safety.

page_title: General Guidance for Missing Doses – Voy
question: How can I change my injection day?
answer: Make sure at least 4 days have passed since your last injection before giving the next dose. This might mean extending the gap between doses longer than the usual 7 days to shift your schedule.

page_title: How do I unsubscribe from marketing communications? – Voy
question: How to unsubscribe to marketing communications?
answer: You can unsubscribe via email by looking for the 'unsubscribe' link at the bottom of any marketing email from us and clicking it to be removed from our marketing mailing list. Alternatively, you can contact us directly by emailing help@joinvoy.com and our team will assist you in unsubscribing.

page_title: How do I unsubscribe from marketing communications? – Voy
question: What happens when you unsubscribe from marketing communications?
answer: You'll be removed from our marketing mailing list and will no longer receive promotional emails or offers from us.

page_title: How do I unsubscribe from marketing communications? – Voy
question: Does unsubscribing from marketing communications affect transactional emails?
answer: Unsubscribing from marketing communications does not affect transactional emails related to your orders or important updates about your account or treatment.

page_title: How do I update my account or subscription? – Voy
question: How do I update my account details?
answer:
You can edit certain details, such as billing method, delivery address and general account preferences by:

1. Logging into your account
2. Clicking Account in the left-hand menu
3. Selecting Account Details

Here, you can change your personal info (email, name, phone number), shipping address, and billing address. If you're changing your shipping address, please make sure to do this before your next order is placed.

page_title: How do I update my account or subscription? – Voy
question: How can I amend my next order date?
answer:
To amend your next order date:

1. Log into your online account
2. Click on Account in the left-hand menu settings
3. Select 'Manage Plans'
4. Choose a date that works for you

Your payment and order will then process on the new date you've selected. Due to time-sensitive administration of our prescription medications, there is a limit of 18 days to how far an order can be pushed back.

page_title: How do I update my account or subscription? – Voy
question: How can I change my treatment or dose?
answer: If you wish to change your treatment or dose, discuss with a member of our medical team by booking a consultation or messaging our Clinical Team on your account through Support -> Messages.

page_title: How do I upload photos? – Voy
question: How do I upload photos during sign up and safety checks?
answer: Once you've signed up to Voy, you'll be asked to complete two tasks: 1) upload a full-length photo of yourself taken that day 2) upload a photo of your ID. You can upload your photos to the tasks located on the Home page of your online account. If you have tasks to complete you'll find them here. If you've been asked to complete a task but can't see any tasks on your account. You can upload photos to your Messages with our Clinical Team on your Support page by clicking the paper clip icon in the text box. If you're still unable to upload your photos, please speak to our Customer Care Team who will be happy to help you upload your photos to your tasks.

page_title: How do I upload photos? – Voy
question: Why do we ask for photos?
answer: Throughout your weight loss journey, we might ask you to upload new photos to help us monitor and review your progress towards your goal weight. This is to make sure we're safely prescribing medication at every step of your journey. Your photos are only viewed by our Clinical Team for the purpose of reviewing your eligibility.

page_title: How do I upload photos? – Voy
question: How can I track my progress?
answer: You can also track your own progress within the Voy app by either submitting your weight or a photo of yourself. Open the Voy app and click on 'Progress' from the menu at the bottom of the screen. Here you can add photos and track your progress. If you decide you'd no longer like to see your photos you can enable 'privacy mode' by clicking on Timeline and then the 'eye' icon in the left-hand corner. You can download the Voy app on both the Apple App Store and Google Play Store.

page_title: Is the information I share with you private? – Voy
question: Is the information I share with you private?
answer: Yes, we take your privacy and security information very seriously. We have designed the platform to comply with all the relevant privacy laws and have implemented security protocols to protect your personal information. Please read our Privacy Policy for more information.

page_title: What is your Returns policy? – Voy
question: What is the cancellation window for prescription medications?
answer: You can only cancel an order up until the point at which the prescription is approved by our medical team.

page_title: What is your Returns policy? – Voy
question: Can I return prescription medications after approval?
answer: Once a prescription-only medication has been approved, we cannot cancel the order or accept a return of the items.

page_title: What is your Returns policy? – Voy
question: What regulations relate to the return of prescription medications?
answer: This policy is in line with the Consumer Protection (Distance Selling) Regulations 2000, which exempts prescription medications from standard return rights.

page_title: What is your Returns policy? – Voy
question: Can non-prescription items be returned?
answer: For non-prescription items, we accept returns up to 14 days after purchase. Please contact our Customer Care Team at help@joinvoy.com for a returns label.

page_title: What is your Returns policy? – Voy
question: What is Voy's commitment regarding prescription items?
answer: While we can't accept returns on prescription items, we're here to support you throughout your treatment. If you have any concerns or questions about your medication, please don't hesitate to reach out to our Clinical Team.

page_title: How does my subscription work? – Voy
question: How regularly will I receive my medication?
answer: Depending on your treatment, your subscription will automatically renew every 28 or 42 days. As we're a subscription-based service, your next pen will automatically be sent to you in line with your treatment plan. So, there's no need to place another order. For Mounjaro, your dose will automatically increase every month up to 10mg, and for Wegovy, your dose will automatically increase up to 1mg. However, please know that each order is subject to clinical approval. Our system will automatically take your payment using the billing method you added to your online account. To check when your last order took place, visit Order History from your Account page.

page_title: How does my subscription work? – Voy
question: What if my subscription says expired?
answer: For safeguarding reasons, our Clinician Team needs to approve your medication before it's sent. Your plan will show as expired on a monthly basis. Your subscription will still be active and renewed unless cancelled.

page_title: How does my subscription work? – Voy
question: What if I reach my goal weight?
answer: If you've reached your goal weight, speak to our Medical Team about the best next steps for you.

To avoid any delays over the holiday weekend, you may receive your medication up to 5 days before your usual renewal date. If this happens, you’ll receive an email notification in advance so you have time to reach out if the timing doesn’t work for you.

page_title: How does the approval process work? – Voy

page_title: Can I change my coach? – Voy
question: Can I change my coach?
answer:
We completely understand that finding the right coach is important for your journey. While you’re not able to make this change on your own, our friendly Support Team is here to help!

Simply send us an email or start a chat in the App, and we’ll take care of the switch for you as soon as possible.

If there’s anything else we can do to support you, just let us know—we’re always happy to help!

page_title: Can I use a prescription from my own GP on your website? – Voy
question: Can I use a prescription from my own GP on your website?
answer: We only dispense medication based on prescriptions generated and authorised by our own prescribers. While we value the expertise of other healthcare providers, we cannot accept external prescriptions.

page_title: Can I use a prescription from my own GP on your website? – Voy
question: Why does Voy have a policy on not accepting external prescriptions?
answer: 1. Consistency: This ensures consistency in our treatment approach. 2. Safety: It allows us to maintain our high safety standards. 3. Regulatory Compliance: This policy helps us adhere to online pharmacy regulations. 4. Comprehensive Care: It enables us to provide a complete care package, including follow-ups and adjustments.

page_title: Can I use a prescription from my own GP on your website? – Voy
question: What are the next steps if I have a prescription from my GP?
answer: If you're interested in joining Voy, you can check if you are eligible by completing our medical questionnaire. Our medical team will then assess whether Voy is right for you. If you have a prescription from your GP: You may want to discuss our services with them. They might be able to provide insights into whether our treatments could be suitable for you. If you're already taking GLP-1 medication, you might be able to continue on the dose you're currently on with Voy.

page_title: Are there any medical conditions that might disqualify someone from participating? – Voy
question: Are there any medical conditions that might disqualify someone from participating?
answer:
At Voy, we prioritize your safety and well-being. While we aim to help as many people as possible on their weight loss journey, certain medical conditions may disqualify individuals from our treatments. 

1. Liver, kidney, or heart failure
2. Pancreatitis
3. Multiple endocrine neoplasia type 2
4. Cancer
5. Type 1 diabetes or diabetic retinopathy
6. Personal or family history of medullary thyroid cancer
7. History of eating disorders (e.g., anorexia, bulimia)
8. History of gallbladder problems
9. History of Inflammatory bowel disease or gastroparesis
10. Allergy or hypersensitivity to the active ingredient or any excipients in our medications.

page_title: Are there any medical conditions that might disqualify someone from participating? – Voy
question: What if I'm not eligible for the treatments?
answer: If you're not eligible for our treatments, you may have other suitable weight loss options that are more appropriate for you. Speak with your GP or a healthcare professional for personalized advice.

page_title: Are there any medical conditions that might disqualify someone from participating? – Voy
question: Why are there restrictions on the medical conditions for participation in Voy treatments?
answer: These guidelines ensure the safety and effectiveness of our treatments. They help us maintain high standards of care and comply with medical regulations.

question: How do I track my order from the 'your order has been dispatched' email?
answer: You'll receive an email with a tracking link from Voy and our delivery partner usually in the evening. Direct tracking is also available on the Royal Mail tracking page using the 'Track your order' button in the email.

page_title: Where is my order? – Voy
question: What does each order status mean?
answer: Pending: Before clinician approval. Approval: Undergoing clinician review. Processing order: Pharmacy Team prepares order. With courier: Order collected by delivery partner or delivered.

page_title: Is this a safe and effective way to manage weight loss? – Voy
question: Is this a safe and effective way to manage weight loss?
answer:
Absolutely! GLP-1 medications, when used alongside our expert coaching, have consistently demonstrated impressive results in helping individuals reach their goals. Within the initial six months of treatment, people have achieved weight loss of up to 10%.

Moreover, you can rest assured that your journey towards better health is not just effective but also safe. These medications, when prescribed and monitored by our medical experts, are generally well-tolerated.

Our medical team is committed to guiding and overseeing your treatment to ensure your safety and success. So, you're not alone on this path to achieving your goals.
